Header.Name: teiHeader
Header.Description: TEI header. Supplies the descriptive and declarative information making up an electronic title page prefixed to every TEI-conformant text. Version 2.5.0. Last updated on 26th July 2013 http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-teiHeader.html

CMD_Element.name: funder
CMD_Element.Documentation: (funding body) specifies the name of an individual, institution, or organization responsible for the funding of a project or text; http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-funder.html

CMD_Element.name: note
CMD_Element.Documentation: date element is actually as mixed content in edition within TEI, but CMD not allowing mixed content, it is proposed to enclose text in note

CMD_Element.name: addrLine
CMD_Element.Documentation: (address line) contains one line of a postal address; http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-addrLine.html

CMD_Element.name: orgName
CMD_Element.Documentation: (organization name) contains an organizational name; http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-orgName.html

CMD_Element.name: street
CMD_Element.Documentation: ntains a full street address including any name or number identifying a building as well as the name of the street or route on which it is located; http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-street.html

CMD_Element.name: postCode
CMD_Element.Documentation: (postal code) contains a numerical or alphanumeric code used as part of a postal address to simplify sorting or delivery of mail; http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-postCode.html

CMD_Element.name: name
CMD_Element.Documentation: (name, proper noun) contains a proper noun or noun phrase; http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-name.html

CMD_Element.name: country
CMD_Element.Documentation: contains the name of a geo-political unit, such as a nation, country, colony, or commonwealth, larger than or administratively superior to a region and smaller than a bloc.

CMD_Element.name: settlement
CMD_Element.Documentation: contains the name of a settlement such as a city, town, or village identified as a single geo-political or administrative unit.

CMD_Element.name: institution
CMD_Element.Documentation: contains the name of an organization such as a university or library, with which a manuscript is identified, generally its holding institution.

CMD_Element.name: repository
CMD_Element.Documentation: contains the name of a repository within which manuscripts are stored, possibly forming part of an institution.

CMD_Element.name: idno
CMD_Element.Documentation: (identifier) supplies any form of identifier used to identify some object, such as a bibliographic item, a person, a title, an organization, etc. in a standardized way.

CMD_Element.name: msName
CMD_Element.Documentation: (alternative name) contains any form of unstructured alternative name used for a manuscript, such as an ‘ocellus nominum’, or nickname.

CMD_Element.name: locus
CMD_Element.Documentation: defines a location within a manuscript or manuscript part, usually as a (possibly discontinuous) sequence of folio references

CMD_Element.name: title
CMD_Element.Documentation: contains a title for any kind of work

CMD_Element.name: docAuthor
CMD_Element.Documentation: (document author) contains the name of the author of the document, as given on the title page (often but not always contained in a byline)

CMD_Element.name: docDate
CMD_Element.Documentation: (document date) contains the date of a document, as given on a title page or in a dateline.

CMD_Element.name: docImprint
CMD_Element.Documentation: (document imprint) contains the imprint statement (place and date of publication, publisher name), as given (usually) at the foot of a title page.

CMD_Element.name: textLang
CMD_Element.Documentation: (text language) describes the languages and writing systems identified within the bibliographic work being described, rather than its description

CMD_Element.name: support
CMD_Element.Documentation: contains a description of the materials etc. which make up the physical support for the written part of a manuscript.

CMD_Element.name: extent
CMD_Element.Documentation: describes the approximate size of a text stored on some carrier medium or of some other object, digital or non-digital, specified in any convenient units.

CMD_Element.name: foliation
CMD_Element.Documentation: describes the numbering system or systems used to count the leaves or pages in a codex.

CMD_Element.name: p
CMD_Element.Documentation: (paragraph) marks paragraphs in prose.

CMD_Element.name: origDate
CMD_Element.Documentation: (origin date) contains any form of date, used to identify the date of origin for a manuscript or manuscript part.

CMD_Element.name: origPlace
CMD_Element.Documentation: (origin place) contains any form of place name, used to identify the place of origin for a manuscript or manuscript part.

CMD_Element.name: date
CMD_Element.Documentation: contains a date in any format.

CMD_Element.name: placeName
CMD_Element.Documentation: contains an absolute or relative place name.

CMD_Element.name: date
CMD_Element.Documentation: contains a date in any format

CMD_Element.name: placeName
CMD_Element.Documentation: contains an absolute or relative place name.

CMD_Element.name: glyphName
CMD_Element.Documentation: (character glyph name) contains the name of a glyph, expressed following Unicode conventions for character names; http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-glyphName

CMD_Element.name: desc
CMD_Element.Documentation: (description) contains a brief description of the object documented by its parent element, including its intended usage, purpose, or application where this is appropriate; http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-desc.html

CMD_Element.name: localName
CMD_Element.Documentation: (locally-defined property name) contains a locally defined name for some property; http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-localName.html

CMD_Element.name: unicodeName
CMD_Element.Documentation: (unicode property name) contains the name of a registered Unicode normative or informative property; http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-unicodeName.html

CMD_Element.name: value
CMD_Element.Documentation: (value) contains a single value for some property, attribute, or other analysis; http://www.tei-c.org/release/doc/tei-p5-doc/en/html/ref-value.html
